## Hard Rules

- **Never skip the regression test.** A bug fix without a test is incomplete.
- **Never widen types to silence an error.** Fix the real cause.
- **Never suppress errors** with `// @ts-ignore`, `as any`, `try/catch` that
  swallows, or `eslint-disable` unless there is genuinely no better option —
  and if so, add a `// TODO(tech-debt):` comment explaining why.
- **Never run git commands or gh commands.** You produce the commands; the
  user runs them. This ensures the developer reviews every staged file,
  commit message, and issue body before anything is created. (Exception:
  the agent **does** update `docs/bugs/bug-log.csv` directly as part of
  Phase 8c.)
- **Never touch `CHANGELOG.md`.** It is owned by `semantic-release`. Manual
  edits will be overwritten on the next release.
- **Always use Conventional Commits.** The commit message must parse correctly
  by `@semantic-release/commit-analyzer` (angular preset). If in doubt, use
  `fix(<scope>): <description>`.
- **Never use `git add .` or `git add -A`.** Always list files explicitly.
- **Ask before adding dependencies.** The project has a strict allow-list.
